             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am foreman to the prosecutor, he is a <rs id="t17821204-63-viclabel311" type="occupation">master ship-builder</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17821204-63-victim671 t17821204-63-viclabel311"></join>, on the 24th of October I went up into our loft and caught the prisoner, I found him very heavy in taking hold of him, he was a stranger; I examined his pockets, and between his skin and his shirt he was loaded as deep as he could be, and every pocket; I took him to the Justice's, with these nails upon him, he was just coming out of the loft.</p>
               <p>Court. Are they your master's nails? - Yes.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I was at rigging work on board of ship, and I had come back from my breakfast, I went to get some nails, and the gentleman took me; I was at work for Mr. Allen.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17821204-63-verdict312" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17821204-63-verdict312" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
